Sorry, I just saw in the data dictionary that leads that are won do not qualify lead as a customer yet.  So conversion rate is actually leads that have qualified as customers, that is leads that have status as "Customer".  Here's the formula for the measure:  Conversion Rate = DIVIDE(COUNTROWS(FILTER(Leads,Leads[Status] = "Customer")),COUNTROWS(Leads))  Here's the explanation for the formula above: COUNTROWS(FILTER(Leads, Leads[Status] = "Customer")): This part counts the number of leads that have a status of "Customer", which indicates that the lead has converted to a paying customer.  COUNTROWS(Leads): This part counts the total number of leads in the dataset.  The DIVIDE function divides the number of converted leads by the total number of leads in the dataset

SUBJECT: Join our webinar with WFP, UNICEF and FAO about impactful UN careers
CONTENT: Hi,  My name is Kristina and I'm the Director of Talent Solutions at Impactpool where we gather top talent to solve global challenges.   I'd like to invite you to our upcoming webinar with WFP, UNICEF and FAO, on September 21 at 16.00. This live event will focus on impactful UN careers, specifically on local job opportunities in Budapest (for Hungarian nationals, and holders of Hungarian work permits).   Join this live event to hear directly from the Chiefs of departments and Human Resources officers of FAO, UNICEF and WFP, who will answer questions regarding their jobs and recruitment processes. The panel will also include special guests who will share their career paths and talk about their experiences at the UN.  If you can't attend live, register to receive the recording. Please feel free to share this in your network.   Register for free here: https://bit.ly/ImpactpoolEvent  Have a great day! Kristina  Kristina Pihlblad Bohnerth Director of Talent Solutions at Impactpool

SUBJECT: World of Mobility- Vialto Partners
CONTENT: Hi Eszter,  Hope this email finds you well.    Excuse the direct approach but I am currently looking to fill a position of a Global Mobility- Tax Associate at Vialto Partners, Hungary and based on your educational background/experience, I thought this could be of an interest to you.    This is a full-time position for the person to join our team in Bucharest, where you would be able to get involved and deliver excellence to clients working in a fast-paced environment with colleagues around the world.   As our new colleague you will have the opportunity to work with international clients and employees and assist them in navigating complex tax and immigration challenges that come along with a globally mobile workforce, getting involved in:   * Drafting tax and social security calculations and tax returns (monthly, quarterly, yearly) for Hungarian and foreign clients  * Preparing application forms and other official documents for different procedures at authorities,  * Administration at authorities  * Keeping contact with Hungarian and international clients, other Vialto offices (e.g. sending salary information requests, payroll instructions, discussion about avoiding double taxation)  * Participation on tax briefings, support of senior colleagues  * Correspondence with the Hungarian and foreign assignees  * Participation in tax advisory work   You can find more information about the vacancy and apply following the link: https://smrtr.io/czGpN    If you are interested in the opportunity, please let me know what day next week, would be the best time for us to speak over the phone.    Thank you.   Best Regards,  Iwona PajƒÖk Senior Recruitment Business Partner at Vialto Partners via Cielo Talent
